02/11/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- A MiG-21 Lancer fighter jet crashed during a training exercise Monday (November 1st) killing two pilots, the defence ministry announced.
It happened near the Transylvanian town of Campia Turzii.
The jet was on a mission to study weather conditions ahead of training flights.
The cause of the crash is under investigation.
(Realitatea, AP, Mediafax, Agerpress, DPA - 01/11/10)
